<h3>What is UCT?</h3>
<ol class="round">
    <li class="one">
        <h5>Getting Started</h5>
        
        To use the UCT, please go to the Login dialogue at the top of the page. New users will need to be authorized before access is allowed. 
        @*<a href="http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=245151">Learn more…</a>*@
    </li>

    <li class="two">
        <h5>Find Academic Programs, Learning Activities, and Competencies</h5>
       
        Users can look up and cross reference different Academic Programs, Learning Activities, and Competencies, study their details, and see their relationships. Administrative users can also edit these relationships to adjust them on a yearly basis.
    </li>

    <li class="three">
        <h5>Connect the Dots and Build Better Programs</h5>
        Administrators and users can look at what's expected from students as they progress through their academic programs and adjust as needed. It's as simple as add, edit, and delete. 
        
    </li>
</ol>
